            <div type="translation">
                <p>Invocation of the servant of the God Christophoros Omotes and his wife Maria</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Good condition. A cross with dots in the angles marks the beginning of the text. The words Χριστοφόρος, καί, συνβίου are misspelled. The painter's writing seems to have been influenced again by spoken language. This is confirmed by the word τῆ σηβίου instead of the correct τῆς συμβίας. Accents and breathings with errors. According to <bibl><ptr target="Mouriki1984"/>,<citedRange> 192</citedRange></bibl> , the donors Christophoros Omotes and his wife Maria financed the mural of Saint Christopher and possibly the depictions of Saints Theodore and Paul which are in the same frame as Saint Christopher. The individual donation it seems that was made at the same period with the main decoration of the church.
</p>
            </div>
